events.name: Florida Gators at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Spencer Ware rushed for 109 yards and two scores, each of LSU's quarterbacks passed for touchdowns, and the No. 1 Tigers comfortably defeated 17th-ranked Florida 41-11 on Saturday.

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron passed for career-highs of 237 yards and four touchdowns and No. 2 Alabama beat Vanderbilt 34-0 on Saturday night.

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw three touchdown passes, Dominique Whaley ran 64 yards for another touchdown and the Oklahoma defense scored three more touchdowns, carrying the No. 3 Sooners to a 55-17 victory over No. 11 Texas on Saturday.

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Brandon Weeden threw for 288 yards and five touchdowns before being pulled out of a lopsided game before halftime, and No. 6 Oklahoma State matched its highest scoring total from the last 94 years in a 70-28 rout of Kansas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Okla. St. puts up 70 on Kansas

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Andrew Luck threw for a season-high 370 yards and three touchdowns, and seventh-ranked Stanford stayed perfect with a 48-7 victory over Pac-12 newcomer Colorado on Saturday night.

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw for a touchdown and ran for another before leaving No. 8 Clemson's 36-14 victory over Boston College with a hip injury Saturday that raised concerns about how long the Tigers could stay undefeated without him.

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Tyler Wilson threw for 262 yards on Saturday night, completing 19 straight passes at one point, leading No. 10 Arkansas to a 38-14 win over No. 15 Auburn.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson sharp to help Arkansas beat Auburn

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Denard Robinson threw for two touchdowns and ran for two more, helping No. 12 Michigan come back from a 10-point halftime deficit to beat Northwestern 42-24 Saturday night to remain unbeaten.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan erases halftime deficit, tops N'western

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Tevin Washington ran for 120 yards and two touchdowns and No. 13 Georgia Tech's least impressive offensive showing of the season was enough to beat Maryland 21-16 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 13 Georgia Tech holds on, nips Maryland

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Taylor Martinez ran for a touchdown and passed for two others while bringing No. 14 Nebraska back from a 21-point second-half deficit, and the Cornhuskers defeated Ohio State 34-27 Saturday night in the biggest comeback in school history.

events.name: Connecticut Huskies at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.shortLinkText: W. Virginia pulls away after half to rip UConn

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: South Carolina quarterback Connor Shaw threw for 311 yards and four touchdowns leading No. 18 South Carolina to a 54-3 win over Kentucky on Saturday.

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Nathan Scheelhaase and A.J. Jenkins hooked up on two long TD passes to lead No. 19 Illinois to a 41-20 victory Saturday at Indiana.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 19 Illinois 6-0 after cruising past Indiana

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Collin Klein had three touchdowns rushing for the No. 20 Wildcats, who nearly blew a big second-half lead against Missouri before holding on for a 24-17 victory and their first 5-0 start since 2000.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klein leads unbeaten Kansas State past Missouri

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Logan Thomas ran 19 yards for a touchdown with 56 seconds to play Saturday, capping a wild fourth quarter as No. 21 Virginia Tech beat Miami 38-35.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late TD run lifts Hokies to wild win vs. Miami

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at Utah Utes

headlines.description: Brock Osweiler passed for 325 yards and three touchdowns and No. 22 Arizona State forced five Utah turnovers to turn a close game into a 35-14 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Osweiler tosses 3 TDs in Arizona State's win

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Tanner Price threw three touchdown passes, Josh Harris rushed for 136 yards and Wake Forest upset No. 23 Florida State 35-30 on Saturday.

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Quarterback Ryan Tannehill ran for two touchdowns and threw for another to lead No. 24 Texas A&M over Texas Tech 45-40 on Saturday night.

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Robert Griffin III ran for a season-high 107 yards, Terrance Ganaway rushed for a career-high 200 yards and three scores and No. 25 Baylor beat Iowa State 49-26 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Griffin III helps No. 25 Baylor run over Iowa St.

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at UAB Blazers

headlines.description: Tyler Russell replaced an ineffective Chris Relf at quarterback and threw three touchdown passes to help Mississippi State beat Alabama-Birmingham 21-3.
headlines.shortLinkText: Backup QB steps in as Mississippi St. routs UAB

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Tailback Giovani Bernard and receiver Dwight Jones each had touchdowns, as North Carolina overcame a slow start to win 14-7 on Saturday against a Louisville team that played without its offensive coordinator.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tar Heels overcome slow start, down Louisville

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description:
Akeem Shavers caught a touchdown 
pass and ran for another score to help Purdue beat Minnesota 45-17
 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minnesota sunk by miscues, Purdue's offense

events.name: Memphis Tigers at Rice Owls
Army Black Knights at Miami (OH) RedHawks

headlines.description: Zac Dysert threw three of his four touchdown passes in the second half Saturday, rallying Miami of Ohio to a 35-28 victory over Army that got Don Treadwell his first victory on a day honoring the Cradle of Coaches' history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dysert's three second-half TDs rally Miami (Ohio)

Air Force Falcons at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Tommy Rees threw four TD passes in the first half, Notre Dame built a big early lead and the Irish rolled to their fourth straight victory Saturday, routing Air Force 59-33.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rees tosses 4 TDs, Notre Dame routs Air Force

events.name: Central Michigan Chippewas at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Mike Glennon passed for 244 yards and four touchdowns to help North Carolina State beat Central Michigan 38-24 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Glennon, NC State rally past Central Michigan

events.name: Pittsburgh Panthers at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Gary Nova threw two third-quarter touchdowns in his first start and Rutgers' ball-hawking defense intercepted four passes with Logan Ryan returning his second of the game 45 yards for a touchdown in a 34-10 victory over mistake-ridden Pittsburgh.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rutgers picks off Pittsburgh four times in romp

events.name: Arizona Wildcats at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon St. beats Arizona for first win of season

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Penn State grounded Iowa's best-in-the-Big Ten passing attack, Silas Redd ran for 142 yards and Matt McGloin capitalized on a fourth-quarter turnover with a touchdown pass in a 13-3 win Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn St. slows Iowa passing attack, wins slugfest

Kent State Golden Flashes at Northern Illinois Huskies

headlines.description: Northern Illinois' defense allowed just 70 yards and recorded seven sacks as the Huskies defeated Kent State 40-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northern Illinois defense dominates Kent State
